name: Rob Bonta
tweet: I am committed to protecting seniors throughout our state, and will aggressively investigate and prosecute those who would target and abuse our elders.     Learn more about my office’s Division of Medi-Cal Fraud and Elder Abuse, and how to contact us.⬇️  https://t.co/pxhNL3tRl9

name: Rob Bonta
tweet: Be advised: In the midst of a pandemic or at any time, CA will not tolerate elder abuse and we will hold those who violate our trust accountable.

name: Rob Bonta
tweet: Unfortunately, recent market consolidation in parts of our supply chain has left consumers and producers to pay the price.   As Attorney General, I’m committed to reining in monopolies for a fair and competitive economy.   https://t.co/vs6S8koN3i

name: Rob Bonta
tweet: Fair market competition protects consumers & our economy. I'll keep fighting to ensure that small farms and businesses aren’t choked out by conglomerates and that the system isn’t rigged against American families.     https://t.co/LGg8ulXlNx

name: Rob Bonta
tweet: Desmond Tutu leaves a lasting legacy of freedom and justice. A champion for human rights, through his love and commitment we saw an end to apartheid and the start of transformational change in South Africa.  May his peaceful embrace on this world live on in perpetuity.

name: Rob Bonta
tweet: #Reproductiverights are under attack across the U.S. but CA won't back down. We're fighting to stop AZ's unconstitutional “Reason Ban”.   The decision to terminate a pregnancy before viability is a personal choice & is protected under the law.   https://t.co/CwqXHaDkMc

name: Rob Bonta
tweet: Plain and simple: A pregnancy shouldn’t be a barrier to someone’s ability to remain in the workforce in the 21st century.  I respectfully urge the #USSenate to pass the Pregnant Workers Fairness Act now!  https://t.co/iQotx0xEaI

name: Rob Bonta
tweet: During this time of uncertainty, it's more important than ever to protect the rights of working Californians.    At CADOJ, we've held major fast-food chains to account and pushed for change across the nation.   The more tools we have in this fight, the better. 3/3

name: Rob Bonta
tweet: Despite the fact that noncompetes are unenforceable under CA law, they are still widespread. In fact, an estimated 45% of businesses use them.   These agreements hurt working families by artificially suppressing wages and limiting people's ability to change jobs. 2/3  https://t.co/i3DfvnYCQ9

name: Rob Bonta
tweet: Lawyers have a duty to follow the law when advising their clients. Period.    I'm proud to support the @StateBarCA's proposal to make that obligation even clearer when it comes to illegal provisions — like noncompete clauses — in employment contracts. 1/3   https://t.co/EV5jRB1lHD  https://t.co/84FVfk2PLj

name: Rob Bonta
tweet: I applaud this move by @POTUS & will continue advocating for student borrowers. I urge @usedgov to maintain the payment moratorium until #studentloan servicing transitions are complete & the risk of COVID-19 stabilizes. Student borrowers cannot afford to weather the double storm.

name: Rob Bonta
tweet: GOOD NEWS! @usedgov has announced that the #studentloan payment moratorium is extended until May 1, 2022.   This is welcome news for over 42M student loan borrowers as our nation continues to address the economic impacts of COVID-19.   https://t.co/uiCibP3bUI

name: Rob Bonta
tweet: GOOD NEWS! @NHTSAgov repealed an unlawful Trump-era rule that declared CA's GHG & ZEV standards preempted.  This rule was ill-conceived from the start. It's going to take all of us, doing our part, to tackle the climate crisis & clean up the air we breathe. https://t.co/lmOJ57ow0l
